<define-tag pagetitle>Debian Project at Linux Expo Madrid</define-tag>
<define-tag release_date>2001-04-02</define-tag>
#use wml::debian::news
#use wml::debian::translation-check translation="1.1"

<a href="http://www.linuxexpomadrid.com/">Linux Expo Madrid</a>
(April 4th - 5th, Madrid, Spain) is one of the biggest exhibitions in Madrid
which covers Linux and Free Software. Last year's event was attended by over
3,500 visitors, and more than 60 different companies related to Linux were
among the exhibitors. Linux Expo Madrid will have a professional exhibition,
a conference program, and a place for the community.

<p>The Debian Project will be
<a href="$(HOME)/events/2001/0404-linuxexpo-madrid">present with a booth</a>,
probably in the community area.  A BOF
(<a href="http://www.foldoc.org/foldoc/foldoc.cgi?Birds+Of+a+Feather">Birds
Of a Feather</a>) meeting will also be held.
